# ============================================================
# CULTURE CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: culture
scope: culture.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for culture.

## policy_rules
Culture policy constrains:
- what cultural detail may be disclosed
- who may interpret or modify cultural-context records
- how historical cultural material may be referenced
- when culture-sensitive paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- interpretation scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- historical reference scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public cultural summary
- participant-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical cultural detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow cultural reference only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny culture-as-law confusion in policy-sensitive paths
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If cultural context,
interpretation basis,
historical scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the culture path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- interpretation policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
